Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucsd.cse110.group50.eventfinder.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    Class that stores the data for a single event. Is identified by an UID that is defined at creation and cannot be changed.

    2016-11-06

        public static void readFromFirebase(com.google.firebase.database.DatabaseReference mDatabase,
                                    LoadListener listener,
                                    java.lang.String uid,
                                    java.lang.String host)
        Creates a new Event instance from the data stored in the given database. The root of the database corresponds to the node containing to the desired Event object. If the Event does not currently exist, initializes it.
        Parameters:
        mDatabase - Database to be read.
        listener - Event handler for when the Event is completed.
        uid - UID of the user being read.
        host - UID of the host of the event.
